# BB Daemon (prove_loop) integration patch
#
# Status: JS side COMPLETE, C++ side NEEDED
#
# ── What was done ──
#
# Patched: ~/.aztec/versions/4.1.3/node_modules/@aztec/bb-prover/dest/bb/execute.js
#
# Added daemon process manager that:
#   1. Spawns one persistent `bb-avm prove_loop` per flavor (ultra_honk,
#      ultra_rollup_honk, ultra_keccak_honk) on first prove request
#   2. Sends prove requests as JSON lines to daemon stdin
#   3. Reads JSON responses from daemon stdout
#   4. Falls back to process-per-proof if daemon crashes or returns error
#   5. Includes `concurrency` in the request for per-circuit thread tuning
#
# Control: BB_DAEMON=0 disables the daemon, reverts to stock behavior.
# Export: shutdownDaemons() can be called for clean process exit.
#
# ── What still needs to be built (C++ side) ──
#
# The `prove_loop` subcommand does NOT exist in any available bb binary.
# It must be added to the barretenberg CLI (bbapi_cli.cpp or equivalent).
#
# Required behavior:
#   - Subcommand: `bb-avm prove_loop --scheme ultra_honk --oracle_hash poseidon2 --ipa_accumulation --disable_zk`
#   - Reads JSON lines from stdin, one per proof request
#   - Input:  {"bytecode":"/path","witness":"/path","output":"/path","vk":"/path","concurrency":4}
#   - Output: {"status":"ok","duration_ms":1234} or {"status":"error","message":"..."}
#   - Keeps SRS, thread pool, and bytecode cache alive between requests
#   - Must flush stdout after each JSON response line
#   - Expected savings: ~800ms/proof from avoiding SRS reload + thread pool init
#
# Implementation sketch for C++:
#   while (std::getline(std::cin, line)) {
#       auto req = nlohmann::json::parse(line);
#       // set HARDWARE_CONCURRENCY from req["concurrency"] if present
#       // reuse cached SRS, thread pool
#       // call existing prove() logic with paths from req
#       // write JSON result to stdout, flush
#   }
#
# ── Architecture notes ──
#
# - 3 prover agents = 3 separate Node.js processes, each gets its own daemon(s)
# - Within one Node.js process, daemons are keyed by flavor string
# - Most proofs use ultra_rollup_honk (BaseRollup, merges, block root)
# - Parity uses ultra_honk, RootRollup uses ultra_keccak_honk
# - The daemon protocol is serial per flavor (one request at a time per daemon)
#   which matches how bb prove works (single-threaded dispatch, multi-threaded internally)
#
# ── To revert ──
# Reinstall aztec node or restore original execute.js from npm.
